commit.message: OSS Automated Fix: Addition of Code of Conduct
Update README with basic authentication example
Add support for basic authentication
Bump version to 0.6.0
Add PEP249 required type definitions
Unsupported functions raiaes NotSupportedError
Define all DBAPI required errors in prestodb.exceptions
Add Cursor#close() and #executemany() required by PEP 249

Set meaningless 5 items to None in Cursor.description

According to PEP249:

> The first two items (name and type_code) are mandatory, the other five
> are optional and are set to None if no meaningful values can be
> provided.

https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0249/#description
Fix SET SESSION support by using http_response.headers
Pass auth module to PrestoRequest for testing auth fail

Add `get_exceptions()` to the Authentication module

so that auth-specific implementation should not be leaked to the presto
client code.
Check requests_kerberos availability right before it's used
Make the library runnable w/ and w/o requests_kerberos
Enable run tests with full dependency including extras_require
Make request_kerberos dependency optional

Use lighter weight six for python3 compatibility

We're seeing issues of `python-future`'s types leaking out of the presto
client and causing bad interactions with other libraries.  `future` wasn't
actually being used for all that much and was easily replaced with (already
used) `six`.

Additionally, I made `typing` and `ipaddress` only install in python2.x, they
are already standard library modules in the other supported python versions.
Fix transaction creation
Add need help? section to the README

commit.message:
unpin requirements

I'd like to propose not strictly pinning dependencies in this package, allowing users of this library to have their own pinned versions instead. If accepted and released, fantastic! If rejected, I'll make a fork (for now) that allows us to relax the dependencies.
